Sentencas: A single phase mixed oxide ion-electron conducting electrochemical catalyst of Ce1-xNixO2-y),is employed as an anode functional reformation layer for a coking-resistant solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) based on oxide ion conducting electrolyte operated in methane and ethanol.
Titulo: A highly coking-resistant solid oxide fuel cell with a nickel doped ceria: Ce1-xNixO2-y reformation layer

Sentencas: The high catalytic activity of Ce1-xNixO2-y oxide for fuel reformation is demonstrated by the excellent cell performances in various fuels at relatively low temperatures (550-650 degrees C).
Titulo: A highly coking-resistant solid oxide fuel cell with a nickel doped ceria: Ce1-xNixO2-y reformation layer

Sentencas: The fast oxygen ions flux and formed steam at anode side are also found to be favorable for hydrocarbon reformation to promote the cell performance and long term stability.
Titulo: A highly coking-resistant solid oxide fuel cell with a nickel doped ceria: Ce1-xNixO2-y reformation layer

Sentencas: At 650 C, maximum power densities of 415 and 271 mW cm(-2) are achieved in methane and ethanol respectively.
Titulo: A highly coking-resistant solid oxide fuel cell with a nickel doped ceria: Ce1-xNixO2-y reformation layer

Sentencas: The resistance against carbon deposition is significantly improved with stable voltage output in a long-term durability operation.
Titulo: A highly coking-resistant solid oxide fuel cell with a nickel doped ceria: Ce1-xNixO2-y reformation layer
